reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Provides other wifi names & options, but slower than main wifi even in a remote location
reviews.reviewText: I was warned about wifi repeaters, but bought one anyway. I set up the repeater in a room well away from the main modem & router. The repeater is easy to set up; provides two additional wifi channels that one can connect to. However, several speed tests showed that the additional wifi channels were noticably slower than the main wifi channel even in the remote room. That is, I was better off just using my primary wifi channel. We don't have any significant need for additional wifi channels, what I was hoping for was that the repeater would provide a stronger signal in the remote room for downloads & uploads; it did not. So for my needs, this wasn't a good buy.
